              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Kyoto University Research Reactor (KUR)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The graphite thermal column (TC-Pn) in KUR.",
                "The nominal neutron flux intensity of TC-Pn is",
                "5.86E+10 (n/cm2/sec) at 1 MW power operation.",
                "The AUTHORs confirmed that the TC-Pn was extremely",
                "thermalized on the basis of Westcott's convention",
                "using neutron flux monitors: Au-197, Co-59, Sc-45,",
                "Cu-63, and Mo-98. (See Fig. 8 in the REFERENCE.)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "73-TA-181",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.99988
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Sample:    Ta Foil    0.006 mmt  1.129+-0.001 mg",
                "Monitor:   Au/Al Alloy wire      4.451+-0.001 mg",
                "           Co Foil    0.005 mmt  0.632+-0.001 mg",
                "           Sc Foil    0.025 mmt  0.405+-0.001 mg",
                "           Cu Foil    0.025 mmt  3.587+-0.001 mg",
                "           Mo Foil    0.025 mmt  1.129+-0.001 mg",
                "The sample and the monitors were irradiated",
                "in the TC-Pn for 30 minutes under 1-MW power operation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity germanium detector, relative",
                "efficiency of 25%.",
                "The gamma-ray peak efficiencies of the Ge detector were",
                "measured using a mixed source AM-8140 (Eckert & Ziegler",
                "Nuclitec GmbH, Germany) : Am-241, Cd-109, Co-57,",
                "Ce-139, Hg-203, Sn-113, Cs-137, Co-60 and Y-88."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Based on Westcott's convention method.",
                "Because the neutron flux in the TC-Pn is well",
                "thermalized (See Fig.8 in the REFERENCE) , epithermal",
                "component in Westcott's convention method was",
                "negligibly small."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The reaction rate of the Ta sample was obtained from",
                "the yield of each gamma ray emitted from the",
                "irradiated Ta sample.",
                "The weighted average of the reaction rates was derived",
                "using 1121-, 1189-, 1221- and 1231-keV gamma rays.",
                "Thermal capture cross section and g-factor were taken",
                "from the REL-REF.",
                "The thermal-neutron flux was derived as",
                " (5.688+-0.091)E+10(n/cm2/sec) using the reaction",
                "rates and the thermal cross section of the monitors.",
                "The cross section of Ta-181 was derived from the",
                "reaction rate of the Ta sample and the",
                "thermal-neutron flux component."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Self-shielding coefficients for thermal neutrons were",
                "calculated from neutron capture cross-sections and",
                "area densities of the sample and the monitors.",
                "The coincidence summing effect was estimated from",
                "the peak-to-total ratios and the peak efficiencies."
              ]
            }
          ],
